SYSTEM DYNAMICS

Straight Acceleration

Both propulsion modules deliver synchronized drive torque with continuous
correction to maintain equal wheel loading.

Cornering

The inside and outside wheels may receive different torque demands to improve
vehicle stability and reduce wheel slip.

Uneven Surface

Independent hydraulic assistance compensates for transient changes in wheel
loading while maintaining propulsion continuity.

Emergency Mode

If one propulsion module is degraded, the remaining module can continue to
provide controlled propulsion, although with reduced total performance.

